LOAD SAMPLE SUPERSTORE ORDERS DATA IN TO POWER BI AND PERFORM THESE TRANSFORMATIONS



1. Change Data Types
Dates are text (08-11-2018), Sales/Profit may import as text.


Order Date → Date

Ship Date → Date

Sales → Decimal

Quantity → Whole Number

Discount → Decimal

Profit → Decimal

Transform → Data Type → Date / Decimal Number

🔹 2. Rename Columns (Standard Naming Convention)

Column names have spaces and slashes (Country/Region).


Order ID → OrderID

Order Date → OrderDate

Country/Region → Country

Sub-Category → SubCategory


Right click column → Rename

 3. Remove Duplicate Rows

CA-2018-152156 appears multiple times (valid at line level).
But if checking Order-level table → remove duplicates by OrderID.


Home → Remove Rows → Remove Duplicates
Select OrderID only

 4. Trim & Clean Text

Some text fields may contain extra spaces.



Customer Name
City
State



Transform → Format → Trim
Transform → Format → Clean

 5. Replace Values (Standardization)

United States could appear as:

US

USA

United States

replace:

USA → United States


Transform → Replace Values

6. Extract Year from Order Date
 Create OrderYear column


Add Column → Date → Year → Year

Example:
08-11-2018 → 2018

 7. Extract Month Name
 Create MonthName


Add Column → Date → Month → Name of Month

Example:
08-11-2018 → November

  Create Shipping Days Column
 Business KPI:

Delivery Time = Ship Date – Order Date



Add Column → Custom Column

Duration.Days([ShipDate] - [OrderDate])

Example:
08-11-2018 → 11-11-2018
= 3 days

 9. Create Profit Margin %
 KPI:

Profit Margin = Profit / Sales



Add Column → Custom Column

[Profit] / [Sales]

Format as Percentage

 10. Create Discount Category
 Categorize Discount

Add Conditional Column:

Condition	Output
Discount = 0	No Discount
Discount <= 0.2	Low
Discount <= 0.5	Medium
Else	High
